# Cloudflare Pages response headers — QuickScale Media
#
# The repo already uses PRODUCTION URLs (quickscalem.com). While we're testing on
# scalequick.cc (a noindexed backup/staging domain), the whole site is set noindex.
#
# AT LAUNCH (attaching quickscalem.com), do TWO things:
#   1) DELETE the "X-Robots-Tag: noindex" line in the /* block below (makes the live site indexable).
#   2) Add Content-Security-Policy + Strict-Transport-Security once the Supabase/Pixel/GA
#      endpoints exist (LAUNCH_PLAYBOOK.md Phase 6). Admin keeps the stricter CSP (PROVISION.md §8).
# To keep scalequick.cc itself permanently out of Google after launch, add a host-scoped
# Cloudflare Transform Rule on the scalequick.cc zone instead (so production stays indexable).

/*
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  Permissions-Policy: geolocation=(), microphone=(), camera=()
  X-Robots-Tag: noindex

# Admin is never indexed, on any domain.
/admin/*
  X-Robots-Tag: noindex, nofollow
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
